it**\n\n1. **Prevent the host shell from expanding variables** – use single 
quotes around the whole argument to `docker exec`.  \n2. **Let the container’s 
shell do the variable expansion** – keep `$HOME` or an absolute path inside the 
single‑quoted string.\n\n```bash\n# Use single quotes around the entire 
argument\ndocker exec -it "$dsh" sh -c \'ps aux > 
