/home/raimondo/agent_test/test1.1.log\'\n```\n\n**Why it works**\n\n* The outer 
single quotes stop the host shell from expanding `$PATH` or `$f`.  \n* The 
container’s `sh` receives `ps aux > $HOME/agent_test/test1.1.log` and expands 
`$HOME` (or just uses the absolute path).  \n* The redirection happens inside 
